It's super late, I know. Couldn't decide on the right words to go with that day.  So here's a long rant from me, please bear with me.

So I decided that no words could ever describe how grateful I am, to be able to make it on that day. 
To my home, mom and dad, I know you guys will never read this, but I'm sorry that I changed my name and added ST behind it. I hope that's enough to make you proud.

To @widyaikhsania thankyou. For everything. My litteral 24 hours. The one that came to me in the middle of the storm like some sort of Asgardian angel. Thankyou. Especially for staying and putting up with a douche like me

To @jhniswara @yobelnovianputra @aryamahendra24 @gedeadiarjana @hadiyanprh, @salimkevin @dzakiaulia_ , maybe I could have gotten a better GPA if I hadn't hung out with you guys so much. But I wouldn't trade those moments for anything! üç∫

And to all that have been a part of these last 4 years, thank you! I wouldn't be who I am today if it weren't because of you guys.

Cheers!

Struggles come daily, everyday we go through things we wish we didn't have to face but reality hits yeah like rain on a sunny day. 
The things we face are actually what makes us humans stronger than we started off as. Every struggle that comes always goes, but as it goes it leaves you with more strength than you even think you have. You may not notice it but others around may. And those people around you who notice the strength you gained from the pain you go through, those people who walked with you through it all, those people are the ones you can call home.

Behind every struggle comes strength, behind strength comes hope, behind hope there is peace.
